:"1380","1404":"1404","1513":"1513","1368":"1368","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1431":"1431","1430":"1430","25 November 1431":"25 november 1431","1409":"1409","22 June 1400":"22 juni 1400","1406":"1406","Venice, Veneto, Italy":"Venezia, Veneto, Italië","Little Dunmow, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Little Dunmow, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","of Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"22 June 1400–25 November 1431":"22 June 1400–25 November 1431","1400–1431":"1400–1431","1401–1431":"1401–1431","1404–1464":"1404–1464","1430–1513":"1430–1513","1368–1406":"1368–1406","1380–1409":"1380–1409","16 May 1406":"16 May 1406","10 May 1409":"10 May 1409","1380":"1380","1404":"1404","1513":"1513","1368":"1368","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1431":"1431","1430":"1430","25 November 1431":"25 November 1431","1409":"1409","22 June 1400":"22 June 1400","1406":"1406","Venice, Veneto, Italy":"Venice, Veneto, Italy","Little Dunmow, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Little Dunmow, Essex, England, United Kingdom","of Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fitzwalter","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English, Irish: relationship name from Anglo-Norman French  <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ (  see  Fitz  ) + the personal name   Walter  , ‘son of  <i>Walter</i>’."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitzwater","meanings":["Irish: altered form of <b>Fitzwalter</b>, a patronymic from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (see   Fitz  ) + the personal name   Walter  , meaning ‘son of <i>Walter</i>’.","History: This is the name of a family of Norman origin, descended from Godfrey, Count of Brionne (died <i>c.</i> 1010). Godfrey's grandson, Richard FitzGilbert, accompanied William the Conqueror and was made Lord of Clare. His great-grandson was Robert FitzWalter, one of the barons who guaranteed the Magna Carta in 1215."]},{"name":"Walter","meanings":["English (of Norman origin), German, Dutch, Polish, Swedish, and Danish: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This personal name was introduced into England both in the reign of Edward the Confessor and by the Normans (in the forms <i>Walt(i)er</i>, <i>Waut(i)er</i>). After the Norman Conquest it soon became one of the most popular personal names in Britain. Compare   Walther  .","Germanized or Americanized form of Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian <b>Valter</b> and Czech <b>Valtr</b>: from the personal name <i>Valter</i>, <i>Valtr</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (from Latin <i>filius</i>), used originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same personal name and then conventionalized as a hereditary surname, or short for a surname of which <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ was the first element, for example   Fitzhenry   and   Fitzroy  .","Altered form of English   Fitch  .","German: from a vernacular pet form of the personal name <i>Vinzenz</i> (see   Vincent  ) or <i>Vitus</i> (see   Vito  , compare   Veit  ). Compare also   Fietz  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Baron William Fitzwalter Baron was born on 22 June 1400, in Henham, Essex, England, United Kingdom, his father, Walter FitzWalter 4th Baron FitzWalter, was 31 and his mother, Baronnes Joan Devereux, was 21. He had at least 1 daughter with Elizabeth Chidiock. He died on 25 November 1431, in Little Dunmow, Essex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 31."},"et":{"22 June 1400–25 November 1431":"22. juuni 1400–25. november 1431","1400–1431":"1400–1431","1401–1431":"1401–1431","1404–1464":"1404–1464","1430–1513":"1430–1513","1368–1406":"1368–1406","1380–1409":"1380–1409","16 May 1406":"16. mai 1406","10 May 1409":"10. mai 1409","1380":"1380","1404":"1404","1513":"1513","1368":"1368","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1431":"1431","1430":"1430","25 November 1431":"25. november 1431","1409":"1409","22 June 1400":"22. juuni 1400","1406":"1406","Venice, Veneto, Italy":"Venezia, Veneto, Itaalia","Little Dunmow, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Little Dunmow, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"22 June 1400–25 November 1431":"22. kesäkuuta 1400–25. marraskuuta 1431","1400–1431":"1400–1431","1401–1431":"1401–1431","1404–1464":"1404–1464","1430–1513":"1430–1513","1368–1406":"1368–1406","1380–1409":"1380–1409","16 May 1406":"16. toukokuuta 1406","10 May 1409":"10. toukokuuta 1409","1380":"1380","1404":"1404","1513":"1513","1368":"1368","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","1464":"1464","1431":"1431","1430":"1430","25 November 1431":"25. marraskuuta 1431","1409":"1409","22 June 1400":"22. kesäkuuta 1400","1406":"1406","Venice, Veneto, Italy":"Venezia, Veneto, Italia","Little Dunmow, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Little Dunmow, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"22 June 1400–25 November 1431":"22 juin 1400–25 novembre 